        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 18 at 11:46PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 1146 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Chetopa, moving northeast at 65 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Frontenac, Cherokee, Beulah, Girard, Pittsburg, Roseland, Chicopee,
Scammon, Carona, West Mineral, Lone Oak, Skidmore, Hallowell, Mccune,
Sherwin, Sherman, Faulkner, Stippville, Weir, and Brazilton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
